<h2>
    Ethics and Conservation in Steelhead Fishing
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Wild steelhead must be released</strong>—look for unclipped adipose fins.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Handle fish gently</strong>: Use barbless hooks and wet hands for release.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Support hatchery programs</strong> and conservation initiatives.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Steelhead are a vulnerable species—ethical practices ensure their survival for future generations.
</p>
