</h2>
<p>
    <strong>Q1: Can I keep wild steelhead in Oregon?</strong><br>
    No. Wild steelhead must be released. Only fin-clipped hatchery fish may be retained.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q2: What's the best month to catch steelhead near Salem?</strong><br>
    January–March for winter steelhead; July–September for summer runs.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q3: Are steelhead hard to catch?</strong><br>
    Yes, but with the right gear and technique, even beginners can succeed.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q4: Is fly fishing good for steelhead near Salem?</strong><br>
    Absolutely! The Santiam Rivers offer several good fly fishing stretches.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q5: What's the best bait for steelhead in this area?</strong><br>
    Roe, shrimp-tipped jigs, and pink worms are proven favorites.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q6: Are there steelhead hatcheries near Salem?</strong><br>
